> library(readr)
> library(dplyr)
> readandfilter = function(filename) {
+     df = read_csv(filename) %>% filter(padj < 0.05) %>% filter(abs(log2FoldChange) > 
+         2) %>% filter(baseMean > 10)
+     return(df)
+ }

> ko_untreated = readandfilter("pairwise-ko-untreated-vs-wt-untreated.csv")

Hippo gene signatures

> library(biomaRt)
> tpm = read_csv("tpm.csv") %>% filter(mgi_symbol != "") %>% na.omit() %>% filter(!duplicated(mgi_symbol)) %>% 
+     as.data.frame()
> rownames(tpm) = tpm$mgi_symbol
> tpm$rowname = NULL
> tpm$mgi_symbol = NULL
> tpm = log2(tpm + 1)
> human = useMart("ensembl", dataset = "hsapiens_gene_ensembl")
> mouse = useMart("ensembl", dataset = "mmusculus_gene_ensembl")
> symbolconv = getLDS(attributes = c("mgi_symbol", "ensembl_gene_id"), mart = mouse, 
+     attributesL = c("hgnc_symbol"), martL = human)
> colnames(symbolconv) = c("mouse", "id", "human")
> target_fn = "../../metadata/piccolo.txt"
> targets = read_csv(target_fn, col_names = c("symbol"))
> targets = targets %>% left_join(symbolconv, by = c(symbol = "human"))
> genes = unique(targets$mouse)[!is.na(unique(targets$mouse))]
> genes = genes[genes %in% rownames(tpm)]
> pheatmap(tpm[genes, ], fontsize = 8, scale = "row", legend = TRUE, color = colorRampPalette(rev(brewer.pal(n = 10, 
+     name = "RdYlBu")))(100))

> markers = read_csv("wt-untreated-markers.csv")
> markers = rbind(markers, read_csv("wt-ccl4-markers.csv"))
> markers = rbind(markers, read_csv("yaptaz-ccl4-markers.csv"))
> markers = rbind(markers, read_csv("yaptaz-untreated-markers.csv"))
> toplot = markers$mgi_symbol
> tpm = read_csv("tpm.csv") %>% filter(mgi_symbol != "") %>% na.omit() %>% filter(!duplicated(mgi_symbol)) %>% 
+     filter(mgi_symbol %in% toplot) %>% as.data.frame()
> rownames(tpm) = tpm$mgi_symbol
> tpm$rowname = NULL
> tpm$mgi_symbol = NULL
> tpm = log(log(tpm + 1) + 1)
> pheatmap(tpm, kmeans_k = 4)

Expressed Venn diagrams

Here we make a Venn diagram of the how many genes are expressed in each condition. We will call expressed genes per condition which have a median TPM > 1 for each condition.

> library(tidyr)
> library(ggplot2)
> library(VennDiagram)
> # ggplot(tpm, aes(tpm)) + geom_histogram() + scale_x_log10() +
> # scale_y_log10() table(tpm$tpm < 1)
> load("deg.rda")
> sampledata = deg[[2]]
> sampledata$sample = rownames(sampledata)
> tpm = read_csv("tpm.csv") %>% gather(sample, tpm, -mgi_symbol, -rowname) %>% 
+     left_join(sampledata, by = "sample") %>% group_by(rowname) %>% mutate(mtotal = sum(tpm > 
+     2)) %>% filter(mtotal > 3) %>% group_by(rowname, gt) %>% summarise(mtpm = median(tpm)) %>% 
+     mutate(expressed = mtpm > 1)
